article.description: Ge'Lawn Guyn scored 27 points and shot 6-for-10 from 3-point range as East Tennessee State rallied from an early deficit and held off Eastern Kentucky 87-81 Friday.
article.headline: East Tennessee erases deficit to beat Eastern Kentucky 87-81
article.linkText: East Tennessee erases deficit to beat Eastern Kentucky 87-81
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Ge'Lawn Guyn scored 27 points and shot 6-for-10 from 3-point range as East Tennessee State rallied from an early deficit and held off Eastern Kentucky 87-81 Friday. T.J. Cromer added 22 points for ETSU (5-5). JaVontae Hawkins buried a 3 with 4:24 left to tie it at 71, but Deuce Bello's dunk 22 seconds later put the Bucs on top. Jarelle Reischel tied it at 79 on a 3 with 1:48 to play before Guyn's 3-pointer gave ETSU the lead for good with 1:28 remaining. Cromer's jumper with 22 seconds left extended the lead to 84-79. Eastern Kentucky missed three 3-point attempts in the last 15 seconds. ETSU overcame an 18-7 deficit early and trailed 36-35 at halftime. Reischel scored 29 points and Hawkins chipped in 23 points and nine rebounds for Eastern Kentucky (8-5). ETSU outshot the Colonels from the field 54.5 percent to 53.1.
